Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop the contents of the @Irish pulled pork{300%grams} packaging into an #oven dish{}.

Cover with #aluminium foil{} and cook for ~{25-30%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @egg noodles{150%grams}.
> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated) (use a #teaspoon{} to easily scrape away the peel).

Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit}, discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim the @courgette{1%unit}, then halve lengthways. Slice widthways into ½ cm thick pieces.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @shallot{1%unit}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the shallot, courgette and pepper to the pan.

Fry until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{6-8%minutes}.

When the water is boiling, add the noodles and cook until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} then return to the pot, off the heat.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and toss to prevent sticking.

When the pork is ready, pour the excess liquid from the oven dish into a #bowl{}.

Use two forks to shred the pork while still in the oven dish.

Add the pork, 2 tbsp of the reserved pork cooking liquid (per 2P), ginger and garlic to the pan.

Cook for ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season to taste with @pepper{to taste}.

Remove the pan from the heat, then add the noodles, @sweet Asian sauce{2%sachets}, @hoisin sauce{1%sachet} and @soy sauce{1%sachet}. Toss to coat and warm through the noodles, ~{1%minute}.

Divide the pulled pork and veg noodles between #plates{}.